OL,6,FThe celebrity auctioneer's parents,
OL,7,Fwho were sitting in the front row of
OL,8,Fthe public gallery, wept and hugged
OL,9,Ftheir son after he was discharged from
OL,10,Fthe dock.
OL,12,FJudge Martin Hurst thanked the jurors
OL,13,Ffor their care in considering the case.
OL,15,FHe then told Hanson: "You have been
OL,16,Ffound not guilty. That is the end of
OL,17,Fthe case. You will hear no more about
OL,18,Fit and you are free to go."
